Modifications
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

SpecOps is a derivative work of Clawforce. Files carried over from Clawforce
have been modified from their original form. Notable project-wide changes
include, but are not limited to:

  * Rebrand from Clawforce / Clawbot / clawlib to SpecOps / SpecialAgent /
    specops_lib (Python distributions, imports, CLI commands, environment
    variable prefixes, Docker images, UI routes, components, and hooks).
  * Addition of plan templates, human-review gates on plan tasks, a user
    dashboard, dark mode, CI pipeline, and reverse-proxy deployment docs.

A more complete, commit-level history of modifications is available in
CHANGELOG.md and in the project's git log.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Agentspan API design references
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The durability, guardrail, and OpenAPI api_tool features in SpecOps draw
on the public API design of the Agentspan project:

    Agentspan
    Copyright (c) 2025 Agentspan
    https://github.com/agentspan-ai/agentspan

The Agentspan project is licensed under the MIT License. SpecOps re-
implements the relevant primitives natively in Python and does not
import or copy Agentspan source code. The following symbol names and
the four-mode failure model are derived from Agentspan and re-used in
SpecOps under independently authored Apache-2.0 implementations:

  * GuardrailResult
  * Guardrail (base type and the three concrete types: callable, regex,
    LLM-judge)
  * @guardrail decorator
  * OnFail (modes: retry, raise, fix, escalate; the latter renamed
    from Agentspan's "human")
  * Position (tool_input, tool_output, agent_output)
  * api_tool / OpenAPI auto-discovery shape

The design rationale and per-symbol attribution are documented in
docs/design/durability-and-tooling.md and docs/adr/0001-agentspan-idea-
adoption.md.
